5. EMPIRICAL TESTS
------------------------------------------------------------

For each candidate stiffness profile we compute

    S(r) = ∫_0^r m(s) ds

or, in the weighted case,

    S(r) = ∫_0^r s^κ m(s) ds

and fit

    log S = A + ν log r

across the observed radial window.

The fitted exponent ν determines whether cumulative stiffness follows
the scaling required to produce the master curve.

The later SPARC tests also evaluated:

    1. local baryonic stiffness loading
    2. weighted cumulative accumulation
    3. master-curve generation from the cumulative field
    4. weighted horizon relations
    5. global stiffness-threshold consistency at R_s.



