8. TESTABLE PREDICTIONS
------------------------------------------------------------

The cumulative-stiffness framework predicts that the master-curve
exponent is controlled by the baryonic loading field together with the
effective accumulation measure.

Consequences:

1. galaxies with steeper baryonic acceleration profiles should exhibit
   smaller effective cumulative exponents

2. galaxies with extended baryonic disks should produce ν closer to 1

3. deviations from the master curve correspond to local variations in
   the effective cumulative-stiffness structure

4. the same weighted operator that generates the master curve should
   also organize the weighted horizon relation across galaxies

5. the turnover radius should correspond to a nearly universal
   cumulative stiffness threshold

       S(R_s) ≈ S_c.



